Feeding a obese child: does not have breakfast and takes meat for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9-13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren are above average and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This again shows how important the environment in which the human being evolves and the models that surround him is.
On the tables of obese children, for example, we find charcuterie 50% more often than in families of children with normal weight.
19% of the obese had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness action "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the big kids the sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% replied that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 pupils from primary schools in Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", action supported by General Health Insurance and Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children is the absence of a proper diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate for example eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - snack-dinner, which is a basic principle of a good diet", says one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and cold meats at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that a healthy development requires some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of the students' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been noted is that one tenth of the population does not have breakfast at all.
Breakfast, however, is the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that the families of obese children consume unhealthy fries more often.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sweet drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned do sports regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food from opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating".
Among their favorite dishes are many cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming is in particular a high preference for sweet lemonade", is indicated in the results of the survey.
For lunch it is the pasta that took the first place right in front of the white meat.
Children did not want starches at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Towards health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness-raising session "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was a determined willingness to move towards a healthy diet", the results of the survey indicate.
For example, the most notable was in the case of sweet lemonade, as children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often checked the questionnaire for white meat and fish as a main dish and would reduce sweet and "knedliky" dishes (Czech speciality of bread meal or potato pellets).
