The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before it was released.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed race series and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be in which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what one attended.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible idleness on the part of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has caracterial problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then in more than 50 races.
The result is that each race is done on another route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are pretty supercroit even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
Well, that's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snow-capped mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition to time with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that reduces your visibility significantly.
Then in the mountains you must be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Besides that, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments you try to exceed the requested number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classical duel with the chronometer) and then wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who are entering the game and trying to make the situation dificient.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
It's more like an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by typing on the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is good as this is because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said that it is negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to look elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
At the diffference of the driving model, that of collisions is not yet to the point.
We don't expect this game to be complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don't have, in a collision with any object, any idea of how your car behaves, so it's not completely good.
During tight exceedances you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy voltiges.
Or you'll find yourself in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
The restart is done so that when you broke your face or you came out in the decor the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and it is necessary to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of route in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that need to be passed in a certain way, otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given location "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or one minute late.
What makes you angry are situations when you see the opponent pass easily between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you must either stand aside and converse or brake them.
It doesn't matter if you go in front of him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This upsets the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collid a good number of times.
It can be understood that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's going on.
And it is equal if it is because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You need to pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change car however most of the time you have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cars for straight motorways and super sports cars with exotic sights on very technical pipelines for example on yaw roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects on-line with the Autolog function, which inter alia compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks).
Your speedometer tells you between 150 and 200 km/hour (presumably) and behind you arrives a metro train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
In writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think of us as fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is of choice.
In order to please as many as possible and especially the young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game makes it feel like it's not over.
Fun is really good, but prepare yourself for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
Velvet students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from the higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts orchestrated on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival seat the Rector Vaclav Hampl", says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir des lycées et classes secondaires which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 14 hours on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Student Velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools and that of the University Charles perform.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Union of Czech Cheers in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
All information can be found on the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
