The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first head, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that many of the world's problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully crafted company culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more "delamented for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
