In the same way IBM has a system of well-developed customer relations.
The company was at first brilliant in the discovery of talents - as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and could thus have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for 30 years and currently holds the position of Chief Sales, Marketing and Strategy Officer.
IBM in recent years has done what is called jamy, brain-storming online from which come many future strategies and innovations.
It is not surprising that he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
