It will be recalled that Michoacán did not approve either his Constitution Policy or his State Electoral Code or his Electoral Justice Act, at the same time as the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the legal deadline for the entry into force of this electoral trial, and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted its publication within the time limits provided for by the Law of the State Official Journal, with the argument that he had some objections.
On the same November 9, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the Local Legislative Power and qualified as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the state representative for constitutional reforms, as it does not have the right to "sanction or challenge".
Interviewed on the possibility of the "vote by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to make partial and total counts of votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, it may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there are no voting minutes and counting in the file of the ballot box is not at the President of the ballot box; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of the votes received in all ballot boxes of the election may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the candidate supposed to be the winner of the respective election and the candidate who obtained the second place in the election is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition from the party representative and/or coalition that presented the second of the candidates reported.
The total count of the vote may also be carried out if at the end of the common count it follows that the difference between the candidate who is supposed to win and that of the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is an express petition from the representative of the political party whose candidate has come out second, in which case the electoral packages which were the subject of the partial count shall be excluded.
It should be mentioned that this is the situation of the election of Morelia, where according to PREP, the difference between first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
