Queen Sofía: "These are instruments for progress and hope"
The Queen emphasises the "preponderant" position of Spain with regard to this type of finance
Spain "has achieved a dominant place at the global level in the role of Microfinance".
Queen Sofía recalled that over the past two decades the country has become the world's second largest donor to this instrument of cooperation, the essence of which lies in the fact that it is an "instrument for social progress, justice and hope in a better future for all humanity, based on trust in the human being".
Yesterday, the Queen inaugurated the V-th World Microcredit Summit in Valladolid with the certainty that "there is no doubt" that this type of operation is "absolutely necessary" to achieve the Millennium Goals set by the United Nations for 2015, and, "especially, in that which aims to reduce to half the volume of people living with incomes under one dollar a day, to which is fixed the "threshold of poverty".
Spain "continues to work" to expand the network of beneficiaries "in all corners of the world, and takes on this task with "responsibility", said Queen Sofía, who hoped that the initiatives and contributions that originated during the Summit, which will last until Thursday, "guarantee the creation of new capacities and better opportunities for the poorest and especially for women", the main beneficiaries of these loans.
